        <h4>Terms & Conditions</h4>
        <div>
            Admission in B.A./B.Sc./B.Com / M. A. 1st Semester will be done on the basis of Class 12 (10+2) Marks (Merit Based). After securing merit candidates have to follow proper procedure to get admission in college.
            <br>
            Admission Form with Bulletin/Brochure can be obtained by depositing Four Hundred Fifty Rupees (Rs 450) in cash from the college counter.
            <br>
            Fully filled Admission form with all attachments will be submitted at college counter. Please take a deposit slip after submitting the admission form.
        </div>
        <b>Documents, need to be attached with admission application form as required for the courses</b>
        <ol>
            <li>
                Photo copy of High School Mark sheet.
            </li>
            <li>
                Photo copy of Intermediate Mark Sheet.
            </li>
            <li>
                Photocopy of Graduation Mark sheet & Certificate.
            </li>
            <li>
                If belong to reserved category, photocopy of cast certificate issued by competent authority.
            </li>
            <li>
                Photocopy of the respective certificate for the surcharge / weightage (if requested).
            </li>
        </ol>
        <div>
            <b>Note–</b> All attachments should be submitted with your signature
        </div>
        <b>Documents required at the time of counseling as required.</b>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Photo copy of High School Mark sheet.
            </li>
            <li>
                Photo copy of Intermediate Mark Sheet.
            </li>
            <li>
                Photocopy of Graduation Mark sheet & Certificate.
            </li>
            <li>
                Character certificate issued by Principal/Head of last Institute.
            </li>
            <li>
                Original of Transfer Certificate issued by Principal/Head of last Institute.
            </li>
            <li>
                Surcharge / Weightage (if requested), the original copy of the certificate required to confirm it.
            </li>
            <li>
                Candidates of Scheduled Caste / Backward Classes/EWS (who have applied under reserved category) should submit the original copy of computerized certificate issued by the competent authority /magistrate.
            </li>
            <li>
                Two Ticket size photo of same type of candidate.
            </li>
            <li>
                The office receipt of the admission application form receiving will be deposited in the bank.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <div>
            Minimum 40 % marks is mandatory in 10+2 for general category who wish to get admission in first semester while this condition would not be applied for the candidates of Scheduled Castes/ Scheduled Tribes and Other Backward Castes.
            <br>
            21 Percent, 2 Percent and 27 Percent seats are reserved for scheduled caste, Scheduled Tribes and backward castes (below creamy layer) respectively.
            <br>
            University provides the facility to appear in examination as ex-student to those who have failed in first semester examination of B.A./B.Sc./B.Com./ M. A.
            <br>
            If any information found incorrect filled by candidate, such students will not be allowed to take admission or her/his admission will automatically be cancelled and disciplinary action will be taken against the student for hiding facts.
        </div>
